address1.$t: Taunton Rd. and Harmony Rd., Oshawa

description.$t:
Adorable little Abby was abandoned and now all she wants is someone to cuddle with!! Could it be you?!

Abby's foster calls her a Super Torti, meaning she is brilliant, can read your mind, and knows exactly what she wants and when she wants it.. so don't argue with her! 

Abby would enjoy a home where she can reside as Queen Kitty and get her humans all to herself!

She has been spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, defleaed and de-wormed.
Abby's adoption fee is $175.00.

If you're interested in giving this beautiful girl her forever home, please contact us at denise.avadurham@gmail.com, or fill out an online adoption application at http://actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html. 

Thank you for considering Abby as your new family member!

address1.$t: Taunton Rd. and Harmony Rd., Oshawa

description.$t:
Audrey appeared at a farm wanting to get in the farmers house, since then she has been in the care of AVA. Audrey unfortunately had to have her tail amputated after being rescued but she has recovered fully. 

She is very playful and loves feather wands. Audrey also loves to run around the house at high speed zipping up and down the hallways. She provides lots of entertainment when she is in a silly mood!

Since her tail surgery, Audrey prefers being close to you versus being handled or held. She will happily sit next to you on the couch for pats and chin rubs! She will purr with approval to let you know she's a happy girl!

Audrey can also get rough when she plays or is stressed so she needs an experienced owner who can read her cues and respect them.

 For this reason she would not be the best with kids,however she is being fostered with teens who are experienced with cats.  She has also been fine with dogs that are familiar and friendly with cats.

Audrey has been spayed, microchipped and is up to date on vaccinations.

Our adoption fee is $175.00 for one cat, $300.00 for a pair.

If you're interested in giving this loving and affectionate cat a forever home, please contact us at denise.avadurham@gmail.com or fill out an online adoption application at http://actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html

Toffee was living under railway cars and old buildings at the train station in Uxbridge.  She came to us very shy, but is learning to trust humans.  Toffee likes getting pats and now purrs.  She loves her food (maybe a little too much, but probably from not having enough when younger).  She loves other cats so would be great in a home with a very tame cat.  With lots of attention and patience she will become a wonderful companion.

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

Sophia is a pretty brown tabby and white cat.  She was relinquished to us because the family had allergies and she has been with us for a while.  She is fiesty and playful but also very sweet.  Sophia is looking for a forever home, which she really needs and deserves.

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

Rupert and his sister were rescued from a multi cat household/hoarding situation.  So he is a little shy, but likes pats and is becoming more trusting in his foster home.  He loves to play and cuddle with his sister Anna so they would really like to be adopted together.

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Neuter, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

Annie & her brother were rescued from a hording household (with multi cats),  Often coming from that situation cats are very shy, but Annie is sweet and very friendly.  She loves to get pats and will talk to you when you pat her.  She loves to cuddle and play with her brother Robert so would really like to find her forever home with him.

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

Indiana is a sweet and playful kitten.  She is very friendly, though a little shy in new situations.  She really, really loves lots of pats, cuddles and always wants attention.  Indy also loves to play with other kitties so needs a home with another kitten, young cat or one of her siblings.  

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

Jolene is an adorable tabby & white kitten.  She is very inquisitive & interested in every toy and treat.  She loves to play with other kittens.  Being from a feral colony she is still a little shy with new people and in new situations but time & attention will bring her round.  Jolene needs to go to a home where there is already a kitten or young cat, or with one of her siblings.

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

description.$t:
Meet Princess, an adult kitty looking for her forever home!

Princess has had a rough start to life and is still working on building trust with humans.  She is hungry for affection but a little unsure of how to enjoy the interaction and not be scared.

Princess would do best in a calm home with an experienced owner who will be very patient and work with her to earn her trust.  We have caught glimpses of a very sweet cat and over time those traits will come to the forefront. 

She also loves to play with feather wands and will swat it with such intensity you will find yourself laughing!

Princess also loves her wet food and will happily accept treats from your hand.

Princess does not enjoy the company of other animals and would do best in a home where she is the Queen of the Castle. 

She has been spayed, microchipped and is up to date on vaccinations.

Our adoption fee is $175.00 for one cat, $300.00 for a pair.

If you're interested in giving this loving and affectionate cat a forever home, please contact us at denise.avadurham@gmail.com or fill out an online adoption application at http://actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html, or stop by her temporary home at Petsmart Oshawa North (891 Taunton Rd. E)

Thank you for considering Princess as your new family member.

 AVA is on the hunt for his perfect forever home with a family that will love him unconditionally!

 He's a pretty calm kitty, he likes to lounge and really loves people. He really is a suck up and loves forehead rubs. YouÃ¢Â€Â™ll hear a super loud purr once you get him going! Sometimes if he's had enough or you move too quickly he may give a gentle nip, so itÃ¢Â€Â™s best for him to be in a home with no young children or other animals. 

HeÃ¢Â€Â™s still getting used to play time, but he had some fun with a wand toy yesterday. It only lasted a couple minutes before he just wanted to hang out again, but watching his big self enjoying himself clumsily swatting at the wand was hilarious!

Jonathan has been neutered, microchipped and is up to date on vaccinations.

His adoption fee is $175.00 .

If you're interested in giving this loving and affectionate cat a forever home, please contact us at denise.avadurham@gmail.com or fill out an online adoption application at http://actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html, or stop by his temporary home at Petsmart Oshawa North (891 Taunton Rd. E)

Lacy came from a bad hording situation.  
She is a sweet girl, is still a little shy but loves to get pats.  With a little time and lots of attention Lacy will become a perfect companion.  Please consider giving Lacy a safe and loving forever home.

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

description.$t:
Meet Molly, Oshawa's resident talker! 

This meow-filled one year old little lady is a beautiful kitty with a lot of spunk!

Molly is a sassy kitty, she loves to have conversations with you and will meow for just about any reason!   She loves to be brushed- you'll probably quickly find yourself having a best friend in her if you brush her often. 

Molly is good with other cats, though we'd recommend a home without small children because of that spunky streak in her. Tunnels are another thing she loves, darting in and out of them before retiring to her post. 

Molly has been spayed, vaccinated and microchipped.

Our adoption fee is $175.00 for one cat, $300.00 if you are adopting two together.

If you're interested in giving this loving and affectionate cat a forever home, please contact us at denise.avadurham@gmail.com or fill out an online adoption application at http://actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html .  You can also come visit her at her temporary home,  Petsmart Oshawa 891 Taunton Rd E

description.$t:
Meet Oscar, also known as Comet!

This adorable boy was rescued from the streets of Toronto at 5 months old, along with his two siblings, Alice (aka Jazz) and Arya. Now that Oscar has spent some time one of our wonderful foster homes being socialized, he is looking for a forever home to call his own! 

Oscar is a still a little shy and would love to be adopted to a person who will spend some time to earn his trust. Once that trust is earned, you will see how sweet Oscar truly is.

When he's not snuggled with his sister, Alice, Oscar likes to play! He is also a very curious boy who likes to explore and watch the world.

Oscar needs to be adopted with a sibling or go to a home with another young cat. He would be thrilled to be adopted with his sister Alice (aka Jazz)!

Oscar has been netuered, microchipped and is up to date on his vaccines.
Our adoption fee is $175, or $300 for a pair.

If you would like to meet Oscar, stop by the adoption centre at Petsmart Oshawa (891 Taunton Rd. E)! You can also fill out an online adoption application for him by visiting: http://www.actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html.  

Thank you for considering Oscar (aka Comet) as your new family member!

description.$t:
Meet Alice, also known as Jazz! She was rescued from the streets of Toronto at 5 months old along with two of her siblings (Oscar, aka Comet amd Arya). Now that Alice has spent some time in one of our wonderful foster homes being socialized, she is ready to find a forever home to call her own! 

Alice is a still shy and unsure of humans  She would do best and blossom in a patient and loving home, with an adopter who will spend time to gain her trust and love.

Alice enjoys the company of other cats, and especially loves hanging out with her brother Oscar. She likes to snuggle next to him for a cat nap and some cuddles.
Alice needs to be be adopted with a sibling or go to a home with another young cat. She would be thrilled to be adopted with Oscar.

Alice has been spayed, microchipped and is up to date on his vaccines.
Our adoption fee is $175, or $300 for a pair.

If you would like to meet Alice (aka Jazz), stop by the adoption centre at Petsmart Oshawa (891 Taunton Rd. E)! You can also fill out an online adoption application for him by visiting: http://www.actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html.  

Thank you for considering Alice as your new family member!

Elli was rescued from a hoarders house after the owner got evicted.  The cats were starving when found by our volunteers.  Elli is a gentle girl with a sweet personality.  She loves other cats so should be adopted to a home where there is already a cat or go with one of her foster siblings.

Adoption fee is $150.00 which includes:  Spay, vaccinations, microchipping, de-worming x 2.  All of our cats have been checked by a veterinarian and come with a health record.  For more information call Jenny at 289 314-1158

This cool looking cat is Elvis. Elvis came to us along with 11 other cats all the way from Quebec. They were removed from a situation where the cat population had gotten out of hand. This super cute guy is also super friendly, super snuggly and super adorable. He loves affection from both people and other cats. Elvis has been neutered, vaccinated and microchipped. Visit Elvis and all his friends at the Pickering Animal Shelter.

This little darling is Tina. She came to us as a stray. You won't believe how sweet and friendly she is! Tina's been spayed, dewormed, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations. Come meet her and her friends at the Shelter in Brougham.

Meet Ella! This 13-year-old girl was recently surrendered to us because her family, unfortunately, could no longer look after her. Ella is a sweetie; however, like most older cats, she is set in her ways living a solitary life. She's never lived with other cats, and will do best in a home where she is the only pet. Despite her age, Ella remains a curious girl who loves to explore. She has been vaccinated, microchipped, spayed, and front-declawed. Please visit Ella at the Pickering Animal Shelter located at Brock Rd and HWY 7.

address1.$t: Taunton Rd. and Harmony Rd., Oshawa

description.$t:
Meet the beautiful Justina! Wow, just look at that gorgeous, shiny coat!!

Justina is a very sweet girl, but is still working on building trust with humans. She is a little unsure of cuddles and human interaction, but blossoms a little more with each and every day. She would thrive in a quiet home with another kitty to play with, and a patient owner who will work with her to earn her trust.

Justina sure does love to play! Springs and jingly balls are among some of her favourite toys to bat, chase and roll around with.. an activity that's just as much fun for her to as it is for you to watch!

And when Justina hears a can of wet food opening, those big beautiful eyes of hers grow even bigger!

Justina has been spayed, microchipped and is up to date on her vaccines.   Her adoption fee is $175.00 and she needs to go to a home that already has a cat or be adopted with one of her friends from the adoption center. 

To meet Justina, stop by Petsmart Oshawa (891Taunton Rd. E). You can also head on over to our website, http://www.actionvolunteersforanimals.com/adopt/adoptionform.html, to fill out an online application.

description.$t: Found on Scugog Line 3 near Highway 12. Scotty is a lovely affectionate 1yr old male cat. Help us find his owner! Scotty is now neutered and vaccinated and ready for a forever home. Come visit and fill out an adoption application in person at the shelter!

Found in Port Perry on Earl Cuddie Blvd. (near McDonalds). Minnie is an approximately 8mos-1yr old female siamese mix cat. She appears to be completely deaf (sometimes occurs in all white animals). Minnie is now spayed and vaccinated, ready for her forever home!

Lewis was surrendered to the rescue when his owner moved and couldn't take him along with her. He is a lovely and friendly, one year old cat who enjoys chilling out with his people as much as he enjoys playing. Lewis has always been kept indoors and has never lived with other animals, though we suspect that he would adjust quickly. He has no behavioural or health issues, uses his litter box faithfully and will make someone a lovely companion. Lewis has an adoption fee of $150 to cover the costs of his vaccines and neuter. He is being fostered in Bradford, ON. Please message us if you'd like to welcome this adorable boy into your home!

MAZDA is looking for a family!

Mazda is a gorgeous 3 year old tortie/black cat hoping to find a home soon. She is one of the clinic cats at Ripley's Animal Hospital in need of a forever family. She needs a quiet, loving home with a kind companion where she will blossom.

Mazda is spayed and vaccinated. 

If you are interested in adopting Mazda, please contact Nicola Ransom-Brown of Uxbridge Cat Rescue: njreb.9705@yahoo.com
